Finally, properties of the sensor locations can be specified with the
--sensor-locations option.  This options specifies a \ref locationsFile
that can control whether sensor locations are feasible or infeasible, and
fixed or unfixed.

For example, if the file \b locations contains
\verbatim
infeasible 193 119 141 207 239
fixed 161
\endverbatim
Then the following example shows how these restrictions impact the solution (compared to the first example above):

\verbatim
../../../bin/sp --path=../../../bin --path=../mod --network=test1 --objective=ec --ub=ns,5 --solver=pico --sensor-locations=locations

