The running time is now less than 1 second.  Using a witness aggregation
threshold of 0.25, we have reduced the running time by three orders of
magnitude, and the TCE of our solution has gone from 26,376.2 to 30,229.1.

We can use witness aggregation for any sp run in which the solver is "pico."


\section Notes

The heuristic solvers do not currently support the "median" performance
measure.  The IP solvers do not currently support "median", "var", or
"tce" performance measures.  The aggregation threshold does not currently
impact the problem formulation used by the heuristic solvers.

This solver interface assumes that event likelihoods are uniform.
The format for specifying non-uniform likelihoods remains unresolved.

